&lt;pre&gt;I assume that the plan is to migrate non-incognito usage to SQLite as well
once we have data on the effect of the migration in the wild. There are
other Incognito oracles so I don't think temporarily adding a new one is
much of a problem. Among other things, doesn't IndexedDB performance
already vary between incognito and non-incognito sessions due to the
in-memory storage implementation?
