&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://wpt.fyi/results/css/css-text/text-justify/text-justify-word-separators.html"&gt;https://wpt.fyi/results/css/css-text/text-justify/text-justify-word-separators.html&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt; is failing in the same way on all browsers? Is the test broken or is there
&gt;&gt; something missing in the implementation?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;
&gt; The css-text specification now includes more characters for word
&gt; separation, and no browsers implement them yet. This also affects the
&gt; &quot;word-spacing&quot; property, so we'd like to ship it separately.
&gt;
&gt; LGTM2
