&gt;&gt;&gt; *Summary*
&gt;&gt;&gt; Support of `text-justify` CSS property Web authors can control how text
&gt;&gt;&gt; is justified when `text-align: justify` is applied by using the
&gt;&gt;&gt; `text-justify` property. For example, they can force justification by
&gt;&gt;&gt; expanding inter-character space even in English text.
