&lt;pre&gt;Dear Blink-dev owners,

I added &quot;Experiment goals&quot; to the Chromestatus, but the
auto-intent-to-ship-mail didn't copy this over. Please see the Chromestatus
for those details &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/4926233538330624"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/4926233538330624&lt;/a&gt;&gt;.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

tldr: The requested OT for &lt;usermedia&gt; is a copy of the initial &lt;permission&gt;
element &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/5125006551416832"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/5125006551416832&lt;/a&gt;&gt;. We deviated
from this initial element by creating two separate ones: &lt;geolocation&gt; and
&lt;usermedia&gt; - element. THe &lt;geolocation&gt; - element is shipped, thus we
created a new chromestatus and OT to ensure continuity for current
developers, who are using the element for usermedia and focus on the
iteration of it.
Thank you and Best,
Minh

