&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/WICG/PEPC/blob/main/explainer.md"&gt;https://github.com/WICG/PEPC/blob/main/explainer.md&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;
&gt; *Risks*
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; *Interoperability and Compatibility*
&gt; There is a risk that this feature fails to be adopted by other browsers.
&gt; This can be mitigated by backwards designing a reasonable fallback
&gt; mechanism so that the element can degrade gracefully if the it's in an
&gt; unsupported environment.
&gt;
&gt; *Gecko*: Under consideration (
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/1245"&gt;https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/1245&lt;/a&gt;)
&gt;
&gt; *WebKit*: No signal
&gt;
&gt; *Web developers*: Positive
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/WICG/PEPC/issues/2#issuecomment-2393820279"&gt;https://github.com/WICG/PEPC/issues/2#issuecomment-2393820279&lt;/a&gt;
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/WICG/PEPC/issues/2#issuecomment-2393861768"&gt;https://github.com/WICG/PEPC/issues/2#issuecomment-2393861768&lt;/a&gt;
